# data-models

Core Data Models:

1. Meeting Model
Importance Score: 90
- Properties:
  - transcript: Multi-source meeting content (Teams, Pocket)
  - signals: Array of extracted business signals
  - template_type: Identifies one of 30+ meeting templates
  - dikw_level: Current position in DIKW hierarchy
  - signals_validated: Tracks signal validation state

2. Document Model
Importance Score: 85
- Properties:
  - content: Document text with version tracking
  - knowledge_refs: Links to related DIKW items
  - tags: Auto-generated semantic tags
  - related_meetings: Array of linked meeting references
  - signal_confidence: Signal extraction confidence scores

3. Relationships
- Meeting-to-Document (Many-to-Many)
  - reference_type: Type of relationship (source, related, referenced)
  - confidence_score: Relationship strength (1-10)
  - semantic_context: Stored embedding for relationship

- DIKW Hierarchy Mapping
  - Maps both meetings and documents to DIKW levels
  - Tracks promotion/demotion history
  - Maintains source references across promotions

4. Signal Relationships
Importance Score: 80
- Links signals across meetings and documents
- Properties:
  - signal_type: (decision, action_item, blocker, risk, idea)
  - source_refs: Array of origin references
  - validation_state: Tracks approval workflow
  - confidence: Extraction confidence score

